  <span id="freeText17863196893487160399" style="display:none">A grand love story and an epic tale of three brothers whose lives are torn apart by war.<br /><br />Paris, 1937. Andras LÃ©vi, a Hungarian Jewish architecture student, arrives from Budapest with a scholarship, a single suitcase, and a mysterious letter he has promised to deliver to C. Morgenstern on the rue de SÃ©vignÃ©. As he becomes involved with the letterâs recipient, his elder brother takes up medical studies in Modena, their younger brother leaves school for the stageâand Europeâs unfolding tragedy sends each of their lives into terrifying uncertainty.<br /><br />From the Hungarian village of KonyÃ¡r to the grand opera houses of Budapest and Paris, from the lonely chill of Andrasâs garret to the enduring passion he discovers on the rue de SÃ©vignÃ©, from the despair of a Carpathian winter to an unimaginable life in forced labor camps and beyond, <i>The Invisible Bridge </i>tells the unforgettable story of brothers bound by history and love, of a marriage tested by disaster, of a Jewish familyâs struggle against annihilation, and of the dangerous power of art in a time of war.<br /><br />Length: <b>27 hrs and 51 mins</b></span>
