  <span id="freeText10835974539071430861" style="display:none">This book is WONDERFUL!!!! <br /><br /><br />Julie Orringer is both a great storyteller and a great writer. Excellent Historical Fiction.<br /><br /><br />UPDATE 2015: Here is another book I read 5 years ago... soooo good. I remember every detail. Read it when it first came out - then a couple years later with my Jewish book club. <br /><br />I'm sitting here - today - reading. while on the bike at the gym at the moment and a GR's sent me a note about how much she loved this too...<br />Then - I had the pleasure to read many of my friends reviews ---( I'm not sure we had been friends on this site yet when area read it) <br /><br />If you've not read it... You just won't be bored for a second. ( actually reminds me of another book I finished just 10 minutes ago). <br /><br />The Debt of Tamar... As far as lush storytelling ..<br /><br />Treat yourself and read all the many great reviews.. <br />Better yet... if in the mood for a page turning historical fiction.. You won't go wrong with this one. <br /><br />And WHY has the author not written another book yet? I'd read her in a second. </span>
