        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer150060368" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12677532079636271811">This is the story of Andras Levi, a young Hungarian Jew who has departed Hungary before WWII to study architecture in Paris. It follows him in life as he falls in love, leaves Paris around the war and through his misery in the Labour Camps of Hungary and The Ukraine. A really touching story that is beautifully written and easy to follow....a real tear jerker at times! I enjoyed how the stories of his friends and family also entwined with his. Interesting to find out that the story is also based </span>
  <span id="freeText12677532079636271811" style="display:none">This is the story of Andras Levi, a young Hungarian Jew who has departed Hungary before WWII to study architecture in Paris. It follows him in life as he falls in love, leaves Paris around the war and through his misery in the Labour Camps of Hungary and The Ukraine. A really touching story that is beautifully written and easy to follow....a real tear jerker at times! I enjoyed how the stories of his friends and family also entwined with his. Interesting to find out that the story is also based on the author's own family stories and most likely her Grandfather's experiences.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12677532079636271811" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

